00:34:44.680 --> 00:34:47.280
The father that you find in J-Ball, right?

00:34:47.280 --> 00:34:52.400
As such as dwell in tents and have cattle, I mean, they had things, they were producing.

00:34:52.400 --> 00:34:57.080
You find the music and the arts, you find the metallurgy, you find the tools that are

00:34:57.080 --> 00:35:00.720
being made, and all these things that are going on.

00:35:00.920 --> 00:35:06.880
Reminds me of the church of the Laodiceans, increased with goods, right?

00:35:06.880 --> 00:35:07.880
You read it.

00:35:07.880 --> 00:35:10.080
Turn over there to Revelation 3.

00:35:10.080 --> 00:35:11.080
Read what it says.

00:35:11.080 --> 00:35:17.120
I'm not making this stuff up.

00:35:17.120 --> 00:35:23.080
They didn't think they needed God, but they did.

00:35:23.080 --> 00:35:28.400
We have people today in our society, in our culture that don't think they need God, but

00:35:28.400 --> 00:35:31.560
they do.

00:35:31.560 --> 00:35:37.960
Can I tell you the sad thing is when it creeps into the house of God.

00:35:37.960 --> 00:35:42.240
Without me, Jesus said, you can do nothing.

00:35:42.240 --> 00:35:50.080
In Revelation 3, in verse number 17, notice what it says, because thou sayest, I am rich

00:35:50.120 --> 00:35:56.600
and increased with goods and have need of nothing.

00:35:56.600 --> 00:36:04.920
Knowest not that thou art wretched and miserable and poor and blind and naked.

00:36:04.920 --> 00:36:09.040
What they thought was quite different than what God knew.

00:36:09.040 --> 00:36:12.080
This isn't what God thought, this is what God knew.

00:36:12.080 --> 00:36:13.880
He's the omniscient God, right?

00:36:13.880 --> 00:36:17.680
He's the one that searches the hearts.

00:36:17.680 --> 00:36:23.400
In Genesis chapter number 4, there's a departure and then there's this description.

00:36:23.400 --> 00:36:29.640
If you simply look at it from a temporal perspective, you could say, oh, look at the advancements

00:36:29.640 --> 00:36:31.720
of this society.

00:36:31.720 --> 00:36:33.860
Look at what they were able to do.

00:36:33.860 --> 00:36:39.700
Look at how they were able to mine those metals and how they were able to produce these tools

00:36:39.700 --> 00:36:47.360
and look at what they were able to accomplish, but they were missing God.

00:36:48.040 --> 00:36:51.160
Here's what I think one of the problems is in our country today.

00:36:51.160 --> 00:36:52.160
We have plenty.

00:36:52.160 --> 00:36:57.160
Can I tell you, in America, we're spoiled rotten in America, we really are.

00:36:57.160 --> 00:36:58.440
I mean, look, I'm glad.

00:36:58.440 --> 00:37:02.240
I like to be comfortable, amen, and I think you do too.

00:37:02.240 --> 00:37:04.200
I like the air conditioning.

00:37:04.200 --> 00:37:08.840
We're spoiled in America.

00:37:08.840 --> 00:37:13.360
Sometimes what happens is we just get full of ourselves and think, I don't need anything,

00:37:13.360 --> 00:37:14.360
we're good.

00:37:14.360 --> 00:37:22.000
And as a whole, as a society, we find that we're living in a day, if the stock market's

00:37:22.000 --> 00:37:26.720
good, if this is good, if that's good, nobody seems to think they need God.

00:37:26.720 --> 00:37:30.600
It could all crash that fast.

00:37:30.600 --> 00:37:37.280
What happened, something interesting, when we were doing that Corvette outreach a week

00:37:37.280 --> 00:37:44.000
ago on Saturday, Brother Sommerdorf said this in his presentation.

00:37:44.000 --> 00:37:49.080
He listed all the things that happened on 9-11, he said, this led to this, one nation

00:37:49.080 --> 00:37:55.960
under God, where after that event, that tragic event on September 11, 2001, we prayed together.

00:37:55.960 --> 00:37:56.960
It was interesting.

00:37:56.960 --> 00:37:57.960
I talked to a man.

00:37:57.960 --> 00:38:00.400
I don't think the man was a saved man.

00:38:00.400 --> 00:38:03.320
And I told him, Brother Sommerdorf was busy, I said, he gives the nickel tour, I give the

00:38:03.320 --> 00:38:06.560
penny tour, I just found out about this this morning, I don't know a whole lot about it,

00:38:06.840 --> 00:38:07.840
but I'll do my best.

00:38:07.840 --> 00:38:12.720
I began to go through the car with him and share some things, and I was pointing to underneath

00:38:12.720 --> 00:38:16.480
the hood, and those of you that were there, you knew, you saw this, how that there were

00:38:16.480 --> 00:38:21.840
really four sections there, and it captured all of the names of those that were killed

00:38:21.840 --> 00:38:24.880
in the flights, the four flights on that day.

00:38:24.880 --> 00:38:29.840
It had all the names of those that died in the towers, those that were first responders,

00:38:29.840 --> 00:38:32.520
and then those that died at the Pentagon.

00:38:32.520 --> 00:38:34.480
And I said this to the man, I said, do you remember where you were?

00:38:34.480 --> 00:38:36.160
You probably weren't even alive.

00:38:36.160 --> 00:38:37.560
Do you remember where you were?

00:38:37.560 --> 00:38:38.920
You weren't alive.

00:38:38.920 --> 00:38:40.800
And I said, I remember exactly where I was.

00:38:40.800 --> 00:38:45.120
Listen, if you were alive on September 11, 2001, you know where you were.

00:38:45.120 --> 00:38:49.960
I said to this man, I said, do you know where you were?

00:38:49.960 --> 00:38:52.520
And he gave me a story of some things that happened, and I don't have time to go into

00:38:52.520 --> 00:38:55.800
it this evening, we're out of time, but here's what he said.

00:38:55.800 --> 00:38:59.040
He said, really, I didn't understand the gravity of the situation.

00:38:59.040 --> 00:39:02.920
I heard some things, but I was busy about doing stuff, and I heard some stuff was going

00:39:02.920 --> 00:39:08.400
on, but I just really didn't really see what was really happening.

00:39:08.400 --> 00:39:12.320
Went in the office, and half of the office was just glued to the news, and the other

00:39:12.320 --> 00:39:16.680
half of the office was just kind of work as normal, we're just doing our thing.

00:39:16.680 --> 00:39:18.880
He said, and then more stuff started coming in.

00:39:18.880 --> 00:39:24.200
I started to see that it wasn't just an aviation accident, this was a purposed thing.

00:39:24.200 --> 00:39:27.200
And here's what he told me.

00:39:27.200 --> 00:39:31.520
He said, I got a group of people, we're in our office, and a group of us got together,

00:39:31.640 --> 00:39:37.440
and we just went to try to find a church so we could pray.

00:39:37.440 --> 00:39:43.160
I don't think the man was saved, but he said, we just wanted to pray.

00:39:43.160 --> 00:39:44.160
Why?

00:39:44.160 --> 00:39:49.400
Because all of a sudden, somewhere in him, he thought, I need God.

00:39:49.400 --> 00:39:52.240
He hadn't thought about that before.

00:39:52.240 --> 00:39:53.240
Right?

00:39:53.240 --> 00:39:56.120
Brother Somersdorf said, there's no atheist in a foxhole.

00:39:56.120 --> 00:40:00.000
I've never been in a foxhole, I don't ever want to be in a foxhole, but I understand

00:40:00.000 --> 00:40:00.840
the analogy.

00:40:00.840 --> 00:40:06.780
When there are bullets flying over your head, it will wake you up and give you an understanding

00:40:06.780 --> 00:40:09.440
of life and death.

00:40:09.440 --> 00:40:15.080
In this culture, this ungodly line of Cain, he had everything going for him.

00:40:15.080 --> 00:40:16.760
Things were progressing.

00:40:16.760 --> 00:40:17.760
Things were advancing.

00:40:17.760 --> 00:40:21.320
But they didn't have God.

00:40:21.320 --> 00:40:26.800
This evening, if we're not careful in America, we see that there's some advancings in technologies

00:40:26.800 --> 00:40:31.640
and financial whatever.

00:40:31.640 --> 00:40:34.680
We're very poor as a nation, honestly.

00:40:34.680 --> 00:40:39.600
But the reality is that we just look at it temporally.

00:40:39.600 --> 00:40:42.000
And we're in the danger of wickedness and evil.

00:40:42.000 --> 00:40:44.260
You see it all around us.

00:40:44.260 --> 00:40:46.840
They legislate wickedness today.

00:40:46.840 --> 00:40:48.040
Amen?

00:40:48.040 --> 00:40:50.480
It's being legislated.

00:40:50.480 --> 00:40:54.320
It's hard to comprehend what's happening in our society.

00:40:54.320 --> 00:40:58.680
They call evil good and good evil.

00:40:58.680 --> 00:41:01.760
We're there.

00:41:01.760 --> 00:41:04.200
And it leads to destruction.

00:41:04.200 --> 00:41:12.240
Oh, how we ought to just pray for our nation, how we ought to ask God to use us to help

00:41:12.240 --> 00:41:18.440
give and promote and propagate the truth of the Word of God.

00:41:18.440 --> 00:41:23.360
For it's only the truth that God said would make men free.

00:41:23.400 --> 00:41:28.840
To the bondage of sin that grips them so tightly.

00:41:28.840 --> 00:41:31.520
This evening, we have the remedy.

00:41:31.520 --> 00:41:32.560
We have the cure.

00:41:32.560 --> 00:41:33.560
We have the gospel.

00:41:33.560 --> 00:41:35.520
We've got the Word of God.

00:41:35.520 --> 00:41:36.520
Amen?

00:41:36.520 --> 00:41:38.920
And it's the ungodly line of Cain.

00:41:38.920 --> 00:41:39.920
Let's pray.

00:41:39.920 --> 00:41:40.920
Father, we love you.

00:41:40.920 --> 00:41:41.960
We thank you for loving us.

00:41:41.960 --> 00:41:45.380
Thank you for your Word.

00:41:45.380 --> 00:41:53.000
Thank you this evening for the opportunity to see a little bit of that which was taking

00:41:53.000 --> 00:41:58.120
place in the early days of human history.

